      "end": 11.12,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 11.7,
      "end": 15.7,
      "text": "Recorded by Christine Doer, the known as Asa, Florida.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 17.32,
      "end": 21.04,
      "text": "Asaps Fables, the Lioness, and the Vixen.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 21.88,
      "end": 28.44,
      "text": "A lioness and a Vixen were talking together about their young, as mothers well, and saying",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 28.44,
      "end": 33.4,
      "text": "how healthy and well-grown they were, and what beautiful coats they had, and how they",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 33.4,
      "end": 34.76,
      "text": "were the image of their parents.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 35.82,
      "end": 38.92,
      "text": "My litter of cubs is a joy to see, said the Fox.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 39.74,
      "end": 44.18,
      "text": "Then she added rather maliciously, but I notice you never have more than one.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 45.06,
      "end": 49.56,
      "text": "No, said the Lioness, grimly, but that one's a lion.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 50.82,
      "end": 52.82,
      "text": "Quality, not quantity.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 54.02,
      "end": 56.94,
      "text": "End of the Lioness and the Vixen.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
